---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../../components/PageHeader.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Brand Identity · Brand Story"
  description="The 10-year origin story of Increments Inc. — why it exists, what it replaces, and how it became what it is today."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="Brand Identity · 02"
    title="Brand Story"
    italicWord="Story"
    lede="Every brand worth building is a reaction to something broken. Increments is ten years of reacting to one thing: founders who needed real software, fast — and couldn't find anyone they trusted to build it."
  />

  <Section title="The origin" kicker="2016 — Before Increments had a name">
    <p>
      In 2016, MSI Shamim kept watching the same scene play out. A founder
      would describe what they needed — a working product, in weeks, not
      quarters. And an agency would quote six figures and twelve months.
      Offshore shops would quote one-tenth the price and deliver something
      that looked right in screenshots but fell apart in production.
    </p>
    <p>
      The middle didn't exist. A founder couldn't hire premium engineering
      without waiting a year to ramp a team. They couldn't trust a cheap
      shop to own the work. And they couldn't afford to be a line item on
      an agency's roster of 200 clients.
    </p>
    <p>
      Increments started as the answer to <em>"what would it look like if
      senior engineering moved at startup speed, and treated every client
      like the only one?"</em>
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section title="The name" kicker="Build in real, shippable increments">
    <Callout variant="note">
      <p>
        The name isn't a flourish. It's the philosophy.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Increments</strong> means we ship small, real, working things —
        a 7-day prototype, a 2-week milestone, a 30-day integration. Not
        12-month waterfall plans with a single ship date at the end. Not PDF
        roadmaps that no one reads. Incremental, observable, shippable progress —
        every week, every sprint.
      </p>
    </Callout>
  </Section>

  <Section title="The first decade" kicker="What a decade of doing this taught us">
    <div class="arc">
      <article class="arc-year">
        <span class="arc-label">2016–2018 · Prove it</span>
        <p>
          The first two years were spent proving that premium engineering,
          delivered founder-direct, could be faster than any agency and more
          trustworthy than any offshore shop. Every client was a referral.
          Every engagement was a bet on the model.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="arc-year">
        <span class="arc-label">2019–2021 · Systematize it</span>
        <p>
          The 7-day prototype became a default. The <em>free audit, then
          decide</em> offer became a default. The <em>24-month locked pricing</em>
          became a default. What was once a set of handshakes became a
          repeatable system — and the first non-referral clients started
          arriving.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="arc-year">
        <span class="arc-label">2022–2024 · Scale it</span>
        <p>
          Partnerships with <strong>Freeletics</strong>, <strong>Abwaab</strong>,
          and a growing list of operator-founders who came back for second
          and third engagements. The team grew. The system held. The brand
          started to feel like a category, not a service.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="arc-year arc-year--current">
        <span class="arc-label">2026 · Ten years in · Anniversary edition</span>
        <p>
          This year we formalize what the first decade produced: a design
          system, a partner program with six tiers, a Founding 25 program
          for the next generation of clients — and a brand that reflects
          the discipline we've always operated with, even when the collateral
          didn't quite match.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Why it matters" kicker="The story isn't decoration">
    <p>
      The brand story isn't a marketing asset. It's the reason every
      decision downstream — how we price, who we hire, what we refuse to
      take on, what we say no to — makes sense.
    </p>
    <p>
      Whenever a team member or partner asks <em>"should we do this?"</em>
      — whether it's a discount, a platform, a hire, a new service line —
      the story is where the answer comes from. If the decision moves
      Increments closer to an agency or closer to an offshore shop, it's
      probably wrong. If it moves us closer to <em>senior engineering,
      founder-direct, real increments, locked pricing</em>, it's probably
      right.
    </p>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .arc {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-10);
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
  }

  .arc-year {
    background: var(--color-surface-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-soft);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    padding: var(--space-12) var(--space-14) var(--space-14);
  }

  .arc-year--current {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-brand-lime);
  }

  .arc-label {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 10.5px;
    font-weight: var(--type-weight-bold);
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-brand-lime);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .arc-year p {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    max-width: none;
  }

  .arc-year strong {
    color: var(--color-text-strong);
    font-weight: var(--type-weight-heavy);
  }

  .arc-year em {
    font-family: var(--font-editorial);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: var(--type-weight-regular);
    color: var(--color-brand-lime);
  }
</style>
